repo_metadata.description: A fully tested, abstract interface to creating OAuth clients and servers.

advisories.title: SimpleGeo python-oauth2 vulnerable to the use of Insufficiently Random Values to generate nonces
advisories.description: The (1) make_nonce, (2) generate_nonce, and (3) generate_verifier functions in SimpleGeo python-oauth2 uses weak random numbers to generate nonces, which makes it easier for remote attackers to guess the nonce via a brute force attack.

advisories.title: SimpleGeo python-oauth2 does not check the nonce allowing replay attacks
advisories.description:
The Server.verify_request function in SimpleGeo python-oauth2 does not check the nonce, which allows remote attackers to perform replay attacks via a signed URL.
The vulnerability does not appear to be patched according to the following [discussion](https://github.com/joestump/python-oauth2/issues/129#issuecomment-895911502).
